Activity: A1 – Discover security concepts used on campus

Objective
The goal of this activity is to observe and analyse security concepts used on campus.

Method
I walked around campus and identified security measures such as CCTV cameras and access card doors.

Findings
I discovered the following security implementations:
1. CCTV cameras - monitor suspicious behaviour and record incidents for future investigations if needed
2. Student access cards - gives access to enter buildings with physical access card locks to prevent unauthorised entry
3. Human security guards - improves staff and students safety and prevent criminal activities
4. Network login authentication to access Unifi - makes sure only authorised users access the network

Security Principle
These systems support confidentiality, integrity, and availability.

Evidence


Reflection
This activity helped me understand how security concepts are applied in real environments.
